{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "67726d11c49e8ef28ee2b3fb", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d7713c52ffa3c944600e3"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "67726ce6d221dc77889e6416", "title": "BITSAT 2024 (Memory Based Paper 3)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "The straight wire $A B$ carries a current $I$. The ends of the wire subtend angles $\\theta_1$ and $\\theta_2$ at the point $P$ as shown in figure. The magnetic field at the point $P$ is\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/bitsat/eIzo0PjwrZuNUPihCK6GCTDX5gBm4fw_IxGyD4vWajA.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "YP9Eq", "text": "$\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{4 \\pi d}\\left(\\sin \\theta_1-\\sin \\theta_2\\right)$", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "lzdul", "text": "$\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{4 \\pi d}\\left(\\sin \\theta_1+\\sin \\theta_2\\right)$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "kefHH", "text": "$\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{4 \\pi d}\\left(\\cos \\theta_1-\\cos \\theta_2\\right)$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "NBvqU", "text": "$\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{4 \\pi d}\\left(\\cos \\theta_1+\\cos \\theta_2\\right)$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "The magnetic field at a point $P$ due to a current carrying straight wire, such that the ends of the wires, makes angle $\\alpha$ and $\\beta$ (see figure) is given by\n$B=\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{4 \\pi d}(\\sin \\alpha-\\sin \\beta)$\nwhere, $d$ is the distance between the point $P$ and wire.\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/bitsat/2CI_LkSVH326lX_ZCnfCzZtly31MBjgQ2LMqfxWopw0.original.fullsize.png\"/>\nIn the given problem, $\\alpha=\\theta_1$ and $\\beta=\\theta_2$\n$\\therefore \\quad B=\\frac{\\mu_0 I}{4 \\pi d}\\left(\\sin \\theta_1-\\sin \\theta_2\\right)$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGBSPYQ17022537", "specialTagging": "", "section_type": "normal", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61602420ae6dd863a9d1d7d8", "6160241f1a832a8dea12fbf0", "616024236098c3dc0cc3e764", "61602422b42cfaef18219875", "616024227e2ba4496fdd4552", "61964c8c8d7ade9f02022966", "61c08987636555dc34527e11", "61e7bd70643383b6c26bfb1d", "61964c8e8811f774a40dd9f1", "62962123b040395dcc21a751", "629f3a9143c2c00ea1d2f857", "629109edc3391b7808eb05af", "61bb820fdb486fa25580e4bd", "629f390c27047111eccefe03", "64eb06c03118f713ecfef077", "66d5853aa75f05ee8564f568", "67921d601d5b5072da5e9a88", "67fdff4f378e1624ea7b6a03", "6809202a3a10446a207fded7"], "cpyqbExams": ["61a8a124e8ce0dc8a5c62d2c"]}, "fetch_status": true}